page.title: 04A TRAFFIC SURVEY
page.content: A traffic survey was carried out on 10th July 1985 at Rampside Roundabout. During the half an hour 53 cars went past. 26 were going in the direction of Barrow. 7 were going to Rampside and the rest were going in the direction, of Ulverston. The average amount of people in the car was 2. Two motorbikes went past and they were both going to Roose. The average people on them was one. One tractor went past twice, one time it was going down to Rampside and the other time it was going up towards Barrow. One person was on the tractor. Four lorries went past. They were all going to Barrow and the average people were 1. One bus went past. It was in the direction of Barrow.
